fields.label: Statement of fitness for work – First certificate

groups.label:
This is the approved form for a first  statement of fitness for work up to 14 days

Section 82(1)(b) of the Return to Work Act requires a claim for compensation be  accompanied by a statement of fitness for work in a form approved by the Authority. This form is the approved form for use by a medical practitioner or another person of a class prescribed by regulation that certifies a worker's capacity for work.

•  Medical practitioner to retain a copy

•  This statement to be given to worker

•  Worker to give this statement to employer with a completed Northern Territory workers compensation claim form
Date of injury or disease first noticed:
Workplace location where injury or disease occurred:
Workers description of the injury or disease:
Workers description of how the injury or disease occurred:
In my opinion the injury or disease is:
In my opinion that as from the date of this statement, the worker is:
Fit to return to work on restricted duties from:
Is this a FIRST and FINAL statement of fitness for work?
